Sentencas: First, functional backbones of LaSrCoO4 +/-delta were built on a dense electrolyte substrate, and then a surface layer of the backbones was converted into La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta shell by in-situ reaction with the infiltrated Con+ ions, thus constructing a hybrid electrode of LaSrCoO4 +/-delta@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta with a core-shell structure.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This was evaluated by X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, transmission electron microscopy, and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with single-phase La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta, this hybrid electrode shows lessened thermal mismatch with electrolyte because of a low thermal expansion coefficient of LaSrCoO4 +/-delta backbones.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Further comparison with single-phase LaSrCoO4 +/-delta shows that it has a lower charge transfer resistance instead owing to the excellent electrical conductivity of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta shell.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As the cathode material of solid-oxide fuel cells, the area specific resistance (ASR) of LaSrCoO4 +
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: /-delta is 0.095 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, showing a fast kinetics towards oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At this level, the electrochemical activity of hybrid electrode increased, and the ASR decreased to 0.03 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density as high as 870 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C was achieved from the electrolyte-supported single cell fabricated with this hybrid cathode.
Titulo: LaSrCoO4±δ@La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ core-shell hybrid as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is quite favorable to use this hybrid electrode in a single cell; its prolonged electrochemical performance only slightly decreases.
